title: Interactive Cooking Support System by using Ubiquitous Sensors
title_en: Interactive Cooking Support System by using Ubiquitous Sensors
abstract: 本研究はユビキタスセンサを用いて調理手順を認識し、利用者の進行に応じた指示映像を自動表示することで調理作業を支援することを目的としている。提案手法は大量のセンサ情報を機械学習で処理し、マルコフモデルによる行動予測と学習ベースの分類器を組み合わせて利用者に適切な指示を提供することを目指している。
abstract_en: This study aims to support cooking tasks by recognizing cooking procedures using ubiquitous sensors and automatically displaying instructional videos according to user progress. The proposed method processes large amounts of sensor data with machine learning and combines behavior prediction with a Markov model and learning-based classifiers to provide appropriate instructions to users.
positioning_summary: 本研究はユビキタスセンサと過去行動データを組み合わせて調理手順を正確に認識することを中心課題とする研究である。本研究は調理中の支援を必要とする利用者を対象として多様かつ大量のセンサ情報から現行手順を推定し次の行動を予測する点に位置づけられている。
positioning_summary_en: This study is positioned around accurately recognizing cooking procedures by combining ubiquitous sensor data and past behavior records. This study targets users who need assistance during cooking and addresses the gap of estimating current procedures and predicting next actions from diverse and large-scale sensor information.
purpose_summary: 本研究の目的は大量のセンサデータと過去の行動記録を考慮して調理手順を正確に認識し、利用者に適切な指示を提供することである。本研究は調理支援を必要とする利用者に対して手順認識と行動予測を通じて支援を提供することを目的としている。
purpose_summary_en: The purpose of this study is to accurately recognize cooking procedures by considering large amounts of sensor data and past behavior records and to provide appropriate instructions to users. The purpose of this study is to assist users who need cooking support by delivering guidance through procedure recognition and behavior prediction.
method_summary: 本システムはユビキタスセンサから得られる大量のデータと過去行動を入力として機械学習で調理手順を認識し、マルコフモデルに基づく行動予測アルゴリズムで次の行動を予測して指示映像を自動表示する設計を採用している。提案された本システムは決定木系の分類器などの学習ベースの認識処理と行動予測を統合して調理支援機能を実装している。
method_summary_en: The system recognizes cooking procedures by inputting large amounts of ubiquitous sensor data and past behavior into machine learning models, and it predicts next actions with a Markov model-based behavior prediction algorithm to automatically display instructional videos. The proposed system integrates learning-based recognition such as decision-tree classifiers with behavior prediction to implement cooking support functionality.
evaluation_summary: 本研究は提案手法の実現可能性を確認するために被験者を用いたユーザ実験で評価を行った。本研究は参加者10名による実験で提案した調理手順認識と行動予測の組合せが実用可能であることを示す結果を得た。
evaluation_summary_en: This study evaluated the feasibility of the proposed method through a user experiment with human subjects. This study obtained results from an experiment with 10 participants that showed the combination of the proposed procedure recognition and behavior prediction was practical.

Title: Interactive Cooking Support System by using Ubiquitous Sensors
Authors: Takuo Suzuki, Akira Tokumasu, Yasushi Nakauchi, Sho Murakami
Year: 2008
Abstract: This study aims to support cooking tasks by recognizing cooking procedures using ubiquitous sensors and automatically displaying instructional videos according to user progress. The proposed method processes large amounts of sensor data with machine learning and combines behavior prediction with a Markov model and learning-based classifiers to provide appropriate instructions to users.
Positioning Summary: This study is positioned around accurately recognizing cooking procedures by combining ubiquitous sensor data and past behavior records. This study targets users who need assistance during cooking and addresses the gap of estimating current procedures and predicting next actions from diverse and large-scale sensor information.
Purpose Summary: The purpose of this study is to accurately recognize cooking procedures by considering large amounts of sensor data and past behavior records and to provide appropriate instructions to users. The purpose of this study is to assist users who need cooking support by delivering guidance through procedure recognition and behavior prediction.
Method Summary: The system recognizes cooking procedures by inputting large amounts of ubiquitous sensor data and past behavior into machine learning models, and it predicts next actions with a Markov model-based behavior prediction algorithm to automatically display instructional videos. The proposed system integrates learning-based recognition such as decision-tree classifiers with behavior prediction to implement cooking support functionality.
Evaluation Summary: This study evaluated the feasibility of the proposed method through a user experiment with human subjects. This study obtained results from an experiment with 10 participants that showed the combination of the proposed procedure recognition and behavior prediction was practical.
